 :tx/rationale "AUDIT-EXT CALIBRATION (from PROJECT_ASSESSMENT Priority 1): Automatic hypothesis outcome detection needed — calibration loop is open. PROBLEM: The hypothesis ledger records predictions via record_hypotheses_with_type() at harvest time. But outcome matching requires explicit :action/outcome datoms. The CLI's braid close should generate these automatically but doesn't wire them to hypothesis entities. Without outcomes: (1) per-type confidence stays at 0.5 prior, (2) minimum-5-per-type threshold never met for most types, (3) mean error degrades because new predictions made against uncalibrated prior, (4) 'trend: DEGRADING' is actually 'trend: UNCALIBRATED'. JUSTIFICATION: This is the single highest-leverage fix for the hypothesis ledger. It closes the calibration loop (OBSERVER-4) which is currently open — violating NEG-010 (no open loops). Every other intelligence feature (routing, concept clustering, inquiry) depends on calibrated predictions. This is the keystone. SOLUTION: When a task is closed via braid close, check if any hypothesis entity references it via :hypothesis/action. If so, generate :action.outcome/followed datoms automatically. Small change: <100 lines in commands/task.rs + harvest pipeline. VERIFICATION: After closing 10 tasks with hypothesis refs, mean error should decrease. Per-type calibration should activate. DEPENDENCIES: Interacts with AUDIT-EXT-HIGH-1 (dimensional mismatch). Both needed for calibration to work. FINDING SOURCE: PROJECT_ASSESSMENT.md Section 6 Priority 1. FILES: crates/braid/src/commands/task.rs, crates/braid-kernel/src/routing.rs. SEVERITY: High. WAVE: 1. EFFORT: 4h."
